All Implemented Interfaces:
com.guidewire.commons.entity.Keyable, com.guidewire.commons.entity.Sourceable, com.guidewire.pl.persistence.core.BeanMethods, Approvable, CreatedViaDelegate, Editable, EventAware, Extractable, KeyableBean, Retireable, Validatable, Versionable, Bean, BundleProvider, Comparable<Bean>
@Generated(value="com.guidewire.pl.metadata.codegen.Codegen", comments="CheckSet.eti;CheckSet.eix;CheckSet.etx") public class CheckSet extends TransactionSet
CheckSet A subtype of TransactionSet which contains a Check. May contain more than one Check if its a multi-payee check (in a CheckGroup) and/or RecurringCheck. It may also contain Reserve transactions if its payments affect reserves (like a Final payment or a payment that exceeds Available Reserves). Submitted as a unit for approval. Each of the payment transactions for all the checks in a checkset also link back to the CheckSet.

    • prepareForCommit

      public ApprovalResult prepareForCommit() throws com.guidewire.pl.system.exception.WorkflowValidationException
      Prepares the previously created check for commit to the database. Call this method after calling resetCheckAndPaymentsToDraft() and performing any modifications to the check, such as adding additional Payments or TransactionLineItems. This methods executes PreSetup Rules, updates TAccounts and also submits the check for approval. If approval is required, an approval activity will be created. Otherwise, the CheckSet will automatically be marked as approved.

      This method is intended to be used only from within Rules, where you will use them to commit modifications made to an already submitted check.

      IMPORTANT:

      • After calling this method, the check may not be modified, except for extension fields.
      • This method should not be called on recurring checks, as programmatic editing of recurring checks is currently not supported. Attempting to do so will result in an appropriate exception being thrown.
      Returns:
      an ApprovalResult object, representing the result of the approval
      Throws:
      com.guidewire.pl.system.exception.WorkflowValidationException
